Provisioning the cluster

1. k8s cluster is provisioned with terraform and linode provider to use linode kubernetes engine

2. linkerd is installed with helm
   # 2a. install linkerd cni plugin:
   linkerd install-cni | kubectl apply -f -

   # 2b. add linkerd helm repo
   helm repo add linkerd https://helm.linkerd.io/stable

   # 2c. install linkerd crds (omit the --create-namespace flag if linkerd namespace is created)
   helm install linkerd-crds linkerd/linkerd-crds \
  -n linkerd --create-namespace --set cniEnabled=true
   
   # 2d. install linkerd-control-plane with generated certificates
   # generate certificates: "https://linkerd.io/2.13/tasks/generate-certificates/#generating-the-certificates-with-step"
   
   helm install linkerd-control-plane \
  -n linkerd \
  --set-file identityTrustAnchorsPEM=ca.crt \
  --set-file identity.issuer.tls.crtPEM=issuer.crt \
  --set-file identity.issuer.tls.keyPEM=issuer.key \
  linkerd/linkerd-control-plane --set cniEnabled=true